<task id="MCI-020" project="M365 Copilot Integration R1">
  <metadata>
    <title>HandoffUrlBuilder Service</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <phase>3</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, handoff, deep-links</tags>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>MCI-010</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Create the HandoffUrlBuilder service that generates deep-link URLs for navigating users
    from M365 Copilot back into the Spaarke platform. The service constructs URLs that open
    specific Code Page wizards and the Analysis Workspace within Dataverse, pre-filling
    parameters so the user lands in the right context without re-entering information.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer experienced with Dataverse navigation, Code Page deep-links, and URL construction</role>

  <goal>
    Deliver a HandoffUrlBuilder service that generates correct, parameterized deep-link URLs
    for all supported handoff targets — wizards and workspace pages — using the
    Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo webresource URL format.
  </goal>

  <constraints>
    - URLs must follow the Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo webresource format: pageType=webresource, webresourceName, data parameter with query string
    - Support all handoff targets: DocumentUploadWizard, SummarizeFilesWizard, CreateMatterWizard, CreateEventWizard, PlaybookLibrary, AnalysisWorkspace
    - Pre-fill parameters (documentId, matterId, containerId, playbook context) in the URL data query string
    - URL-encode all parameter values
    - Service must be stateless and registered as singleton
    - Follow ADR-010 DI minimalism — single registration
    - Construct URLs that work when opened from both Teams and Copilot surfaces
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/ai-m365-copilot-integration/design.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-m365-copilot-integration/spec.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-006.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Review design.md wizard deep-link section to understand all handoff targets and their required parameters</step>
    <step order="2">Define an enum or constants for supported handoff targets (DocumentUploadWizard, SummarizeFilesWizard, CreateMatterWizard, CreateEventWizard, PlaybookLibrary, AnalysisWorkspace)</step>
    <step order="3">Create HandoffUrlBuilder.cs with a BuildUrl method that accepts a target type and parameter dictionary</step>
    <step order="4">Implement URL construction using the Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo webresource format with proper encoding</step>
    <step order="5">Add overloaded convenience methods for common handoff scenarios (e.g., BuildAnalysisWorkspaceUrl(matterId, documentIds))</step>
    <step order="6">Register service as singleton in DI</step>
    <step order="7">Add unit tests verifying URL format and parameter encoding for each handoff target</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read</tool>
    <tool>Write</tool>
    <tool>Edit</tool>
    <tool>Glob</tool>
    <tool>Grep</tool>
    <tool>Bash</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Features/Agent/HandoffUrlBuilder.cs</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    - HandoffUrlBuilder is registered as singleton in DI
    - BuildUrl method generates valid Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo webresource URLs
    - All six handoff targets are supported with correct webresource names
    - Parameters are URL-encoded in the data query string
    - Convenience methods exist for common handoff scenarios
    - Unit tests verify URL format correctness for each target type
    - Missing required parameters throw ArgumentException with descriptive message
    - URLs work when opened from M365 Copilot deep-link actions
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
